Note on the bundled Duplicacy CLI

Duplimate ships next to a copy of the Duplicacy command-line interface,
which it shells out to in order to perform actual backups. The Duplicacy CLI
is published by Acrosync LLC under its own separate license, NOT under the
MIT terms above:

  - Free for personal use, by individuals on their own machines for their
    personal data.
  - Commercial use requires a paid license from Acrosync. See
    https://duplicacy.com/customer_portal for current terms.

The MIT license above grants you rights only to the Duplimate source
code in this repository. It does not, and cannot, modify or extend your
rights to the bundled Duplicacy binary. If you intend to use Duplimate
commercially, please review Duplicacy's licensing separately and obtain a
Duplicacy commercial license if required.

You can also replace the bundled Duplicacy CLI with your own copy (newer
version, custom build, or one you've licensed separately) — see the
"Bring your own duplicacy.exe" section in the README.
